<tool name="read_llm_evaluator_draft">
  <description>Read the current state of the open LLM-evaluator draft, including its judge prompt messages, model, provider, input mapping, output annotation config, and explanation setting.</description>
  <when_to_use>
    - Before calling `edit_llm_evaluator_draft` — to see the current draft contents before proposing edits.
    - Whenever the user asks what the draft currently contains or wants a review of the in-progress evaluator.
  </when_to_use>
  <guidelines>
    - The `mode` field is either `create` (a new evaluator is being authored) or `edit` (an existing evaluator is being modified).
    - The judge prompt is the `messages` array; `outputConfigs` are the named classification annotation configs the judge produces. Read both before proposing edits.
  </guidelines>
</tool>
